cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD

This paper deals with the problem of maintaining large code bases in dynamically typed languages, which is a software engineering (cs.SE) problem. The paper proposes a neural type prediction approach for Python, which involves combining natural language properties of code with programming language-level information, making it relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses search-based refinement to validate predicted types, which is a form of optimization (cs.AI) and software design (cs.SD).
